    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today\u2019s slate prioritizing high-ceiling matchups against soft-throwing rotations. The primary play of the day is **Tyler Soderstrom**, whose 76.84 efficiency score is the highest on the roster; a favorable matchup against Cecconi, combined with a premium #3 spot in the order and a park factor boost, makes him an essential start. **Trevor Story** (73.82) follows closely, benefiting from a rare combination of an elite matchup against Arrighetti and a slow-delivery opponent that effectively green-lights his stolen base potential. **Vinnie Pasquantino** (70.89) is also a standout, as his platoon edge against Hancock is the most significant situational advantage in our lineup, yielding a massive +14% boost to his base projection.\n\nThe most difficult benching decision involved **Travis Bazzana**, who narrowly missed the starting cut with a 46.50 score. While his elite xwOBA of 0.408 suggests he is on the verge of a breakout, his sub-optimal platoon matchup against a lefty forced the optimizer to favor **Alex Freeland**\u2019s volume. Elsewhere, **Corbin Carroll** remains a core start despite a tougher matchup against Imanaga; his projection is buoyed by his #3 order placement and the need to chase stolen base upside, though his score is tempered by the risk of facing a high-efficiency left-handed starter. We are closely monitoring weather reports for the **Trevor Story** game, where wind blowing out provides a legitimate power upside that could see him outperform his projection. With **Jose Caballero** falling below our 40-point floor due to an ugly matchup against Bradish, we are banking on the high-floor reliability of our active starters to sustain our category production.",
